@axhav 
And even if that stub is removed, then upstream proton will probably run into the issue described by @jpgay earlier about missing gstreamer plugins.

@kisak-valve
Do you happen to know why Proton doesn't ship with the bad and ugly gstreamer plugins? License/Patent issues that makes You unable to? Or just want to play it safe?
If so, is it possible to statically link the plugins from the Host if they're present?

It seems like [this patch](https://github.com/GloriousEggroll/proton-ge-custom/commit/9683753583beb2557a890312e67d81ebcb82e83c) from GloriousEggroll's [Proton-6.8-GE-1](https://github.com/GloriousEggroll/proton-ge-custom/releases/tag/6.8-GE-1) fixes the issue for many. I seem to personally not be able to launch the game under anything except proton-experimental, but some have suggested this is a denuvo issue.

If the game launches for you, videos will work for you under that version. Do note that this requires backing up your games wine prefix folder, deleting the original, and then copying your saves back in (or download from steam cloud) as the current prefixes break due to the wine 6.8 update, as well as controller hotplugging being broken due to that same update 

@kisak-valve is this something that can be incorporated or are there legal/logistical issues that would prevent this?

> I was able to open main menu and character select in offline mode, no tinkering outside of using proton experimental. However, the game crashes on character creation

@kingpingu I faced the same issue, which was solved after [increasing the number of file descriptors](https://github.com/ValveSoftware/wine/blob/proton_6.3/README.esync).

Now game runs perfectly except for online, which doesn't currently work because probably EAC.

@joni999 Which proton version? proton no not have wine wayland.  
And `PROTON_ENABLE_WAYLAND=1` and `PROTON_ENABLE_HDR=1` are for other proton fork like ge-proton or proton-em.

Nvidia gpu also need [This](https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/vk-hdr-layer-kwin6-git). (Which `ENABLE_HDR_WSI=1` enable).

@Shearerbeard Thank you for the report. 
This appears to have been a mesa issue that have already been fixed again on latest main.

@zany130 I have tried loading into a save game a whole bunch of times on my desktop but have been unable to reproduce so far.
Tested with Proton 8.0-2, kernel 6.3.6, AMD 7900XTX with mesa 23.0.3 and a AMD 7950x
